htvcenter-server.conf setup for postgres database :

htvcenter_DATABASE_TYPE="postgres"                  # supported are : mysql, oracle, db2, ...
htvcenter_DATABASE_SERVER="localhost"               # ip-address of the database server
htvcenter_DATABASE_NAME="htvcenter"                   # database name
htvcenter_DATABASE_USER="htvcenter"                   # database user
htvcenter_DATABASE_PASSWORD="test"                  # database password


Hints for compiling php + postgress support :

Use the standart php with postgres support
start postgres and create db by :

su - postgres
-bash-2.05b$ dropdb htvcenter
DROP DATABASE
-bash-2.05b$ createdb htvcenter
CREATE DATABASE
-bash-2.05b$ dropuser htvcenter
DROP USER
-bash-2.05b$ createuser -a -D -P htvcenter
Enter password for user "htvcenter":
Enter it again:
CREATE USER
-bash-2.05b$


